snippet.title: Can These Contestants Survive the Grueling Canteen Challenge? (Clip) | I Survived Bear Grylls | TBS
snippet.description:
The contestants have crawl around a muddy swamp for bugs. In the desert, there are 10 cups: rotten coconut milk, dirty swamp water, monkey urine, camel saliva, smashed eyeballs, yak blood, snail mucus, elephant poo juice, snake bile, and rabbit dropping stew. The contestants have to find fluids and match it to the right canteen. Watch more I Survived Bear Grylls on TBS.

The stripper arrives, but turns out to be a hooker. Rachel takes Phoebe along to dinner with Rachel’s dad, because she is afraid her dad will be really angry when she tells him she’s pregnant. Jefrick ‘Knife Ninja’ Barrios is a self taught modern day ninja. It is his first time performing in front a large audience and the judges can feel he’s Barrios is nervous. For his act, he has come up with new dangerous tricks including the hair dart where he concealed a knife in his ponytail and sticks his target. He taught himself flips, break dancing, and knife throwing. He is here to make his two daughters proud. Will Barrios be able to stick it to the competition?

About Go Big Show:
Bert Kreischer hosts Go Big Show with celebrity judges T-Pain, Rosario Dawson, Jennifer Nettles and Cody Rhodes. Go Big Show showcases supersized talents on a scale never before seen on television. Featuring monster trucks, alligator trainers, stunt archery and other radical feats, the program celebrates daring acts alongside personal, behind-the-scenes stories from the challengers as they battle head-to-head to impress the judges and advance toward the finale’s ultimate $100,000 prize.

snippet.title: Go Big Show: T-Pain Is Not Impressed By Magician Velasco’s Dangerous Escape Act (Clip) | TBS
snippet.description:
Magician, Fernando Velasco, went big with his escape, but was not able to impress one of the judges, T-Pain. For his act, he is bound in a straitjacket and secured by his feet upside down below a spring loaded 5000 pound steel trap. And not to mention, the whole thing is set on fire. If he doesn’t get out within 60 seconds, the trap will slam shut with the same force of a bite of a great white shark.
